Project Status Update

• Conducted comprehensive research on key factors affecting solar energy output, including weather conditions, panel orientation, system capacity, geographic location, and environmental losses

• Identified and documented critical variables that influence power generation efficiency and performance metrics

• Designed and developed a custom API framework using FastAPI to support prediction testing and validation

• Established project architecture with dedicated machine learning (AIML) and frontend modules

• Created sample datasets and integrated loss factor calculations into the prediction pipeline

• Set up infrastructure for handling prediction requests with essential parameters (latitude, longitude, system size, tilt angle, azimuth, shading factor, and loss values)

Development is currently ongoing on the core prediction engine. The foundation is solid, and we're building on this to move toward production-ready capabilities.
